<h2>The print command</h2>
<p>It is traditional to start with printing hello world when using a new programming language.</p>
<p>Make a new file and type print("Hello World!")</p>
<b>Make sure you have the ("") after print or else you will get a syntaxerror.</b>
<p>Run your file and this will appear.<p>
<p>Hello World!</p>
<p>The world says hello back by the way!<p>
<h2>Fancy Functions</h2>
<h2>What is a function?</h2>
<p>A function is a definition of a command,sometimes multiple commands,here is an example:</p>
<p>def hi():</p>
    <p>print("hiiiiiiiii")</p>
<p>hi()</p>
<p></p>
<p>Now you can type hi() anywhere you want in your code and it will do its asscociated command(s).</p>
<h2>The input command</h2>
<p>Making a form in python?This tutorial is for you.</p>
<p>Type input("What is your name?")</p>
<p>Do you want to add more to this line of code?Simply put name =  before the input.Then press enter and add print("Hello",name")</p>
<p>Now run your code,It will ask for your name and then say hello to you</p>
